MBS User Data Ingest Sessions (Collection)

Retrieve all the active MBS User Data Ingest Sessions managed by the NEF.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-mbs-ud-ingest/v1/sessions

Request the creation of a new Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
Request Body schema: application/json
required

Contains the parameters to request the creation of a new MBS User Data Ingest Session at the NEF.

mbsUserServId
required
string
required
object or null non-empty

Represents one or more MBS Distribution Session(s) composing the MBS User Data Ingest Session. The key of the map shall be any unique string encoded value.

Array of objects (TimeWindow) non-empty
object (RepetitionRule)
object (MBSUserServAnmt)
Deprecated

Represents the MBS User Service Announcement currently associated with the MBS User Data Ingest Session.

object (UserServiceDescription)

A description of a single MBS User Service.

mbsUserServiceAnmtUrl
string (Uri)

String providing an URI formatted according to RFC 3986.

object (MbsDistSessFailureSets)

Represents one or several set(s) of MBS Distribution Session specific failure information.

object non-empty

Contains the MBS Distribution Session(s) for which the provided MBS Service Area was only partially accepted by the MB-SMF and the corresponding retained (reduced) MBS Service Area. The key of the map shall be a string set to the same value received from the NF service consumer within "mbsDisSessInfos" attribute to enable the identification of the concerned MBS Distribution session.

suppFeat
string (SupportedFeatures) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]*$

A string used to indicate the features supported by an API that is used as defined in clause 6.6 in 3GPP TS 29.500. The string shall contain a bitmask indicating supported features in hexadecimal representation Each character in the string shall take a value of "0" to "9", "a" to "f" or "A" to "F" and shall represent the support of 4 features as described in table 5.2.2-3. The most significant character representing the highest-numbered features shall appear first in the string, and the character representing features 1 to 4 shall appear last in the string. The list of features and their numbering (starting with 1) are defined separately for each API. If the string contains a lower number of characters than there are defined features for an API, all features that would be represented by characters that are not present in the string are not supported.

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-mbs-ud-ingest/v1/sessions

Request the update of an existing Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
sessionId
required
string

Identifier of the Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Contains the updated representation of the Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

mbsUserServId
required
string
required
object or null non-empty

Represents one or more MBS Distribution Session(s) composing the MBS User Data Ingest Session. The key of the map shall be any unique string encoded value.

Array of objects (TimeWindow) non-empty
object (RepetitionRule)
object (MBSUserServAnmt)
Deprecated

Represents the MBS User Service Announcement currently associated with the MBS User Data Ingest Session.

object (UserServiceDescription)

A description of a single MBS User Service.

mbsUserServiceAnmtUrl
string (Uri)

String providing an URI formatted according to RFC 3986.

object (MbsDistSessFailureSets)

Represents one or several set(s) of MBS Distribution Session specific failure information.

object non-empty

Contains the MBS Distribution Session(s) for which the provided MBS Service Area was only partially accepted by the MB-SMF and the corresponding retained (reduced) MBS Service Area. The key of the map shall be a string set to the same value received from the NF service consumer within "mbsDisSessInfos" attribute to enable the identification of the concerned MBS Distribution session.

suppFeat
string (SupportedFeatures) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]*$

A string used to indicate the features supported by an API that is used as defined in clause 6.6 in 3GPP TS 29.500. The string shall contain a bitmask indicating supported features in hexadecimal representation Each character in the string shall take a value of "0" to "9", "a" to "f" or "A" to "F" and shall represent the support of 4 features as described in table 5.2.2-3. The most significant character representing the highest-numbered features shall appear first in the string, and the character representing features 1 to 4 shall appear last in the string. The list of features and their numbering (starting with 1) are defined separately for each API. If the string contains a lower number of characters than there are defined features for an API, all features that would be represented by characters that are not present in the string are not supported.

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-mbs-ud-ingest/v1/sessions/{sessionId}

Request the modification of an existing Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
sessionId
required
string

Identifier of the Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

Request Body schema: application/merge-patch+json
required

Contains the parameters to request the modification of the Individual MBS User Data Ingest Session resource.

Array of objects or null (TimeWindow) non-empty
object or null (RepetitionRuleRm)

Represents the same as the RepetitionRule data type defined in 3GPP TS 26.517 but with the OpenAPI nullable property set to true.

object or null non-empty

Contains the requested modifications to one or more MBS Distribution Session(s) composing the MBS User Data Ingest Session. The key of the map shall be any unique string encoded value.

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-mbs-ud-ingest/v1/sessions/{sessionId}
